result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

ADDRESS INFO for Jordan L. Henke
Current: W3674 Cty Rd A, Stetsonville, WI 54480 United States  (Effective: 08-03-2016)
Prior: 142 S. Washington Avenue #a, Medford, WI 54451

Defendant Jordan L. Henke in court.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea agreement put into the record. Victim is in the courtroom.  Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.  Court finds defendant freely and voluntarily waives right to an attorney.  Attorney Tlusty amends 16CM42 to Misd. Disorderly Conduct - 947.01.  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to the amended charge.   Plea colloquy.  Plea freely, voluntarily and intelligently; factual basis exists.  Court finds defendant guilty of DC - 947.01.  Court dismisses and read in Case No. 16CM50.   In 16CM42 the court orders court costs; DNA sample and surcharge; letter of apology to the victim due within one week of plea and sentencing and preapproved by victim witness cordinator.  The costs are to be paid at the rate of $25.00 a month beginning August 12, 2016. Appeal rights given to defendant.   - rt
Plea/sentencing hearing on August 2, 2016 at 02:30 pm.
Pre-trial conference on July 6, 2016 at 02:30 pm.
Order for Appearance at Settlement Conference; Report to Court on Results of Settlement Conference.

*Defendant shall not leave the State of Wisconsin without prior notice to and written approval of the Court.  Must report to the Taylor County Sheriff's Office for Booking Procedure.  Defendant shall have no contact with W.D.M. - dob:  6-20-1994.

Defendant Jordan L. Henke in court.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court informs defendant of charges and penalties. Court enters a plea of not guilty on defendant's behalf.   Court orders a $500.00 signature bond; booking and no contact with W.D.M. - dob:  6-20-1994.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for June 24, 2016 at 09:30 am.  - rt
